description: {"blocks":[{"key":"cbfhb","text":"In mass-spectrometry-based interaction proteomics on-bead digestion protocols are commonly applied after affinity-enrichment due to their simplicity and high efficiency. However, on-bead digestion often leads to strong background signals due to co-digestion of the bead-bound ligands such as streptavidin or antibodies. We present an effective, rapid and low-cost method to specifically reduce the peptide signals from co-digested matrix ligands. A short pre-incubation of matrix beads with Sulfo-NHS-Acetate (S-NHS-Ac) leads to acetylation of free amines on lysine side-chains of the bead-bound ligands making them resistant to Lys-C-mediated proteolysis. After binding of bait proteins to the acetylated beads we employ a two-step digestion protocol with the sequential use of Lys-C protease for on-bead digestion followed by in-solution digestion with trypsin. The strong reduction of interfering ligand peptides improves signal strength and data quality for the peptides of interest in liquid chromatography mass spectrometry (LC-MS). steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"k29d","text":"Wash beads 3x with 100µl Reaction buffer, using the magnetic rack. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":25,"length":15}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7crt8","text":"Remove supernatant after the final wash.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"201m1","text":"Add 19 µl Reaction buffer and 1 µl Sulfo-NHS-Acetate (100 mM) to obtain a final concentration of 5 mM Sulfo-NHS-Acetate. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":10,"length":15}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3bhd5","text":"Incubate 1h at room temperature with gentle mixing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7i0ah","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cppo2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ekqsf","text":"Discard supernatant and wash 3x with 100 µl Quenching buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":44,"length":16}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bc5r3","text":"Use directly or store in 100 µL Storage buffer at 4°C for later use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":32,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"32t4a","text":"This step is not part of the protocol and will depend on the experiment, as for example BioID, enrichment via GFP and GFP-nanobodies, etc. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7frfq","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dikkt","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ev78","text":"Be aware that detergents as for example Triton X100 or Tween 20, can be used during these steps but should be removed by repeated washing with detergent-free buffer. Even small amounts of detergent can strongly interfere with chromatography and mass spectrometry and thus should be avoided by all means. We usually recommend five washes with a detergent free buffer before continuing to the on-bead digest protocol. Alternatively, clean-up protocols that are capable of reliably removing detergents could be used after digestion.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e4d72","text":"Prepare all reagents and materials as specified in Materials.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ftbi","text":"Remove remaining wash buffer from beads. Add 150 µL ABC buffer, gently mix and transfer the beads to a 0.2 mL PCR tube and discard supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"95uhm","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9nf8v","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1johu","text":"The volumes specified in the following steps work depend on initial bead volumes and thus might have to be adjusted accordingly. The volumes specified in this protocol work for up to 30 µL GFP-trap magnetic agarose or 200 µL of streptavidin magnetic beads (see Materials).","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bngkh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bv9nt","text":"Add 50 µL of 1 M urea in ABC buffer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":25,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3cj2r","text":"Add 2 µL DTT stock solution to reach a final concentration of 10 mM. Incubate for 30 min at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":9,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7v02g","text":"Add 2 µL IAA stock solution to reach a final concentration of 20 mM. Incubate for 30 min at room temperature in the dark.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":9,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d2mld","text":"Quench remaining reactive IAA by adding 1 µL DTT stock solution (half the amount used in step 9) and incubate for 10 min at room temperature in the dark. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":45,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9kocq","text":"Add 1.5 µL (150 ng) Lys-C solution and digest over night at 25°C in the dark.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":20,"length":14}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"drbsp","text":"Transfer supernatant to a new PCR tube. Add 1.5 µL (150 ng) Trypsin solution and digest at 37°C for 5h.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":60,"length":16}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7idtd","text":"Acidify sample by adding 3 µL 10% TFA to reach a final concentration of approximately 0.5%. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":34,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"28nm","text":"Proceed to desalting using according protocols (e.g. C18 StageTips or similar). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
